The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) is considering granting waiver to Edo State governor, Godwin Obaseki and his deputy, Philip Shuaibu. This comes as indications have emerged that the party might hold a National Executive Committee (NEC) this week to ratify the defection of the governor and his deputy’s to the party. Obaseki is expected to defect to the PDP in the next few days following his resignation from the APC on Tuesday.